    "body" : "<p>Use:</p>\n\n<pre><code>List&lt;String&gt; x = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;(Arrays.asList(\"xyz\", \"abc\"));\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>If you don't want to add new elements to the list later, you can also use (<a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/util/Arrays.html#asList%28T...%29\">Arrays.asList</a> returns a fixed-size list):</p>\n\n<pre><code>List&lt;String&gt; x = Arrays.asList(\"xyz\", \"abc\");\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Note: you can also use a static import if you like, then it looks like this:</p>\n\n<pre><code>import static java.util.Arrays.asList;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>...</p>\n\n<pre><code>List&lt;String&gt; x = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;(asList(\"xyz\", \"abc\"));\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>or</p>\n\n<pre><code>List&lt;String&gt; x = asList(\"xyz\", \"abc\");\n</code></pre>\n"
