  "title" : "How to declare an ArrayList with values?",
  "body" : "<p><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/12321177/arraylist-declaration-java\">ArrayList or List declaration in Java</a> has questioned and answered how to declare an empty <code>ArrayList</code> but how do I declare an ArrayList with values?</p>\n\n<p>I've tried the following but it returns a syntax error:</p>\n\n<pre><code>import java.io.IOException;\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\n\npublic class test {\n    public static void main(String[] args) throws IOException {\n        ArrayList&lt;String&gt; x = new ArrayList&lt;String&gt;();\n        x = ['xyz', 'abc'];\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
